### Vinyl vs Aluminum Casement Windows: Technical Specification Summary

#### Thermal Performance (Double-Glazed Low-E, Industry Averages)

| Parameter | Vinyl (Multi-Chamber, Fiberglass-Reinforced) | Aluminum (Thermally Broken) | Aluminum (Non-Thermally Broken) |
|-----------|---------------------------------------------|----------------------------|--------------------------------|
| NFRC U-Factor | 0.27 – 0.35 | 0.40 – 0.55 | 0.65 – 0.80 |
| SHGC | 0.22 – 0.30 | 0.25 – 0.35 | 0.35 – 0.50 |
| Frame Conductivity | ~0.17 W/mK | ~0.5 – 1.0 W/mK | ~205 W/mK |
| Condensation Resistance | High | Moderate | Low |
| Energy Star Most Efficient 2025 | Most qualify | Top-tier only | Rarely |

#### Structural & Durability
- **Design Pressure (DP) Rating**: Both can achieve 50–70 psi with reinforcements (Miami-Dade).
- **Corrosion Resistance (ASTM B117)**: Vinyl: 5,000 hrs zero pitting. Aluminum: Requires PVDF coatings + stainless hardware for coastal use; galvanic corrosion risk.
- **Impact Resistance**: Vinyl homogenous; scratches do not reveal substrate. Aluminum softer; dent and chip prone.

#### Cost Comparison (36"×60" Casement, Installed)
- Material: Vinyl $250–400; Aluminum $400–650.
- Installation Labor: Vinyl $150–200; Aluminum $200–300.
- Annual Maintenance: Vinyl $0–5; Aluminum $20–50.
- 10-Year Total Cost: Vinyl ~$2,800–3,500; Aluminum ~$4,200–6,000.
- Expected Lifespan: Vinyl 25–40 yrs (no maintenance); Aluminum 30–50 yrs (requires maintenance).

#### Recommendations
- For 90% of projects (coastal, humid, mixed-climate): Specify vinyl casements.
- Aluminum only when spans >6 ft or narrow sightlines required.

